        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 30 at 2:15PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 214 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles southeast of Hereford, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Dawn, Hereford, and Buffalo Lake.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
